00:18:14.339 --> 00:18:17.890
brutally honest, so saying the truth more than you

318
00:18:17.890 --> 00:18:21.849
should, maybe. Um, SO we often use white lies

319
00:18:21.849 --> 00:18:25.660
or little uh courtesies to make life easier, uh,

320
00:18:25.729 --> 00:18:28.000
that don't create much of a problem, we hope.

321
00:18:28.010 --> 00:18:30.689
Um, SO that would be honesty, courage is the

322
00:18:30.689 --> 00:18:34.540
same thing. It's somewhere between Um, cowardice on the

323
00:18:34.540 --> 00:18:39.770
one hand and um brashness or rashness, let's say,

324
00:18:39.939 --> 00:18:43.500
that's a better word, rash, um, that we don't

325
00:18:43.500 --> 00:18:49.500
take account of risks or possible outcomes. Um. And

326
00:18:49.510 --> 00:18:52.339
what the virtue measures mostly do is when you

327
00:18:52.339 --> 00:18:55.739
look at them, more is almost always better. Um,

328
00:18:55.979 --> 00:18:58.300
AND so that's, that's been a difficult challenge for

329
00:18:58.300 --> 00:19:00.420
us to find a way to measure that middle

330
00:19:00.420 --> 00:19:04.810
ground. Um, SO, so measurement's a very big challenge.

331
00:19:05.189 --> 00:19:07.959
Um, I think. Some of the answers to this

332
00:19:07.959 --> 00:19:12.479
problem are to get other reports, not just self-report,

333
00:19:12.530 --> 00:19:15.400
but to get others to say, let's say I'm

334
00:19:15.400 --> 00:19:18.599
the subject of interest, maybe we get my wife

335
00:19:18.599 --> 00:19:21.479
and a friend or a family member to also

336
00:19:21.479 --> 00:19:24.589
say what they think my strengths or weaknesses are.

337
00:19:25.900 --> 00:19:27.439
So that's one way to do it. Another way

338
00:19:27.439 --> 00:19:31.829
to do it is to ask people questions over

339
00:19:31.829 --> 00:19:34.709
a period of time. So maybe I might ask

340
00:19:34.709 --> 00:19:38.609
the virtue questions um twice a day or 3

341
00:19:38.609 --> 00:19:42.420
times a day for 2 weeks. Um. And that

342
00:19:42.420 --> 00:19:45.140
is still self-report, but it tends to be more

