00:20:32.390 --> 00:20:36.349
us to get develop the sophistication and clarity that

358
00:20:36.349 --> 00:20:38.349
we need to have. But I think it's gotten

359
00:20:38.349 --> 00:20:40.349
a good start. There are many, many studies of

360
00:20:40.349 --> 00:20:45.300
virtue, and it's, it's, it's documented now that we

361
00:20:45.300 --> 00:20:47.859
can measure it and that that it's pretty much

362
00:20:48.109 --> 00:20:50.390
what I would call a scalar concept. People have

363
00:20:50.390 --> 00:20:53.920
more and less of it. Um, THE, uh, research

364
00:20:53.920 --> 00:20:59.119
so far does not show that the, um, Um,

365
00:20:59.229 --> 00:21:02.479
the deception bias that people worry about. There's a

366
00:21:02.479 --> 00:21:03.959
little bit of it, but there isn't a lot

367
00:21:03.959 --> 00:21:07.119
of it, no more than anything else. Um, AND

368
00:21:07.119 --> 00:21:09.959
particularly if you do, uh, this measurement I talked

369
00:21:09.959 --> 00:21:14.650
about with, uh, uh, having someone answer questions multiple

370
00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:16.319
times a day over the course of a couple

371
00:21:16.319 --> 00:21:20.410
of weeks, um, We find that there's a pretty

