00:22:21.170 --> 00:22:26.420
to a sort of moral relativism or anti-moral realist

389
00:22:26.420 --> 00:22:27.880
stance or not?

390
00:22:28.660 --> 00:22:32.459
OK. Yeah, that's, I think it's an important question

391
00:22:32.459 --> 00:22:36.660
about the relativism because there's no doubt that virtues

392
00:22:36.660 --> 00:22:39.500
do vary by culture. They vary by time as

393
00:22:39.500 --> 00:22:43.339
well. So if we look at, let's say, warrior

394
00:22:43.339 --> 00:22:46.859
cultures, for example, Homer is a really big example

395
00:22:46.859 --> 00:22:50.130
for Aristotle, and it's a useful example for us.

396
00:22:50.339 --> 00:22:52.099
So if we look at the virtues in the

